Daud Olatunji The Special Assistant  to the Governor on Student Affairs,  Azeez Adeyemi, on Saturday said the Dapo Abiodun administration  in Ogun State had  rescued   the  collapse of education sector  of the state. Adeyemi insisted that the education was in a shambles when Abiodun became governor of the state. Adeyemi said the governor was able to revive the education sector by discussing with stakeholders. He   said  the crises  in the  Tai Solarin University  of Education, Ijagun,   and Moshood Abiola Polytechnic, Abeokuta, before Abiodun’s  administration came on board were resolved. Adeyemi  said,  “Our government is laying a solid foundation for quality education . We are building a new model for unparallel standard of education.” Copyright PUNCH.
